<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="F" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Fawn3" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Fawn,</orth> vb. 1) to wag the tail: <cit><quote>as the grim lion --eth o'er his prey,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 421" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 421</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>when he --s, he bites,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.290" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 290</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.6.38" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 6, 38</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 5.1.41" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. V, 1, 41</bibl>.<lb />2) to wheedle, to cringe, to be overcourteous: <cit><quote>thy --ing smiles,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.1.158" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. III, 1, 158</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.62" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 62</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.3.42" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 3, 42</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.252" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 3, 252</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.1.45" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 1, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.2.67" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 2, 67</bibl> (Ff <emph>feigning</emph>). With <emph>upon</emph> (== to court servilely and in the manner of a dog): <bibl n="shak. son 149.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 149, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. pp 421" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 421</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.2.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. IV, 2, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.204" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 1, 204</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.170" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 170</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 3.2.130" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 130</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 5.1.33" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 33</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.4.35" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 4, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.1.75" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C IV, 1, 75</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.8.49" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 8, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 3.4.51" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. III, 4, 51</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 1.2.75" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 2, 75</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>